            <h2>How Honest Drain handles exterior drain service</h2>
            <p>Every visit follows a structured approach so you understand the condition of your drainage system and exactly what work is needed.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="trust-stack">
            <article><span>01</span><div><h3>Walk the property</h3><p>We map every drain, downspout, and outlet on your property. We identify the symptom areas and trace the drainage paths to understand where the system is failing.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>02</span><div><h3>Clean and test</h3><p>Grates are pulled, basins are vacuumed, and lines are jetted. We run water through the system and document what flows where — and what does not.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>03</span><div><h3>Camera inspection when needed</h3><p>For underground lines that are not responding to cleaning, we run a camera to identify root intrusion, collapsed sections, or crushed pipe.</p></div></article>
            <article><span>04</span><div><h3>Honest recommendation</h3><p>Cleaning fixes most exterior drain problems. When repair is needed, we explain the scope and price it with flat-rate pricing before any excavation begins.</p></div></article>
